{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀσπάζομαι</b>, <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>aorist</i> ἀσπάσσατο[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “epigram Gr.” 990.9\">Refs</a>]:—<b>welcome kindly, greet,</b> τινά[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, etc.: frequently with _dative_ modi, δεξιῇ ἠσπάζοντο ἔπεσσί τε μειλιχίοισι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.542; χερσίν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.35, +others; ἁδυπνόῳ φωνᾷ 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 2.25\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μεγάλως ἠσπάζοντο αὐτόν <b>received</b> him <b>with</b> great <b>joy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.122, compare 3.1; παρὰ τὴν πόσιν φιλοφρόνως ἀ. [prev. author] 2.121. δ; εὖ νιν ἀσπάσασθε 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 524\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: frequently with no modal word, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 596, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially as the common form on meeting, Στρεψιάδην ἀσπάζομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1145, compare “Pl.” 1042 (see. Scholia), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 273c; αὐτὸν ἠσπάζοντο καὶ ἐδεξιοῦνθ᾽ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 752\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πόρρωθεν ἀ. <b>salute</b> from a distance, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Charmides” 153b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρόσωθεν αὐτὴν ἁγνὸς ὢν ἀ. I <b>salute</b> her at a respectful distance, i. e. keep away from her, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 102, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 499a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. ταῖς κώπαις, of the <b>saluting</b> of ships, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 76\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ἀ. τινὰ βασιλέα <b>to hail</b> or <b>salute as</b> king, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 4.39: _metaphorically_, ἀ. συμφοράν\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] <b>to bid</b> the event <b>welcome,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 587. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> <b>take leave of,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tr.” 1276\">Refs</a>]; τὰ ὕστατα ἀ. <b>take a</b> last <b>farewell,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.39. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__c</b></Level4> as a formula in closing letters, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Rom.16.22, 23, “BGU” 1079.33 (1st c.AD), etc. \">NT+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> from the modes of salutation in use, <b>kiss, embrace,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 607; ἀ. τοῖς στόμασι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Romulus” 1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of dogs, <b>fawn,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.3.9, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 376a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>cling fondly to,</b> ἴσον σ᾽ ὡς τεκοῦσ᾽ ἀσπάζομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1363, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.3.2; ἐγὼ ὑμᾶς ἀ. καὶ φιλῶ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 29d: _metaphorically_, φιλεῖν καὶ ἀ. τὸ ἄδικον [prev. author] “Lg.” 689a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of things, <b>follow eagerly, cleave to,</b> ἀ. τὸ ὅμοιον, οἶνον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Smp.” 192a, “R.” 475a, compare 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 11.44 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of dogs, ἀ. τὰ ἴχνη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 3.7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> ἀ. ὅτι.. <b>to be glad</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 324. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>to be ready to</b>.., εὐωχεῖσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vita Apollonii” 2.7, compare 31, “VS” 2.25.4. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>](<i>active</i> ἀσπάζω in letters (cf. I. C), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1158.18 (3rd c.AD), +others, compare ἀσπάζομαι· ἀσπάζω, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0782","accentedUnicode":"ἀσπάζομαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0783","matchingForm":"ἀσπασμός","stepTransliteration":"aspasmos","gloss":"salutation","_zh_tw_Gloss":"問安","_es_Gloss":"saludo","_zh_Gloss":"问安"},{"strongNumber":"G4685","matchingForm":"σπάω","stepTransliteration":"spaō","gloss":"to draw","_zh_tw_Gloss":"就拔","_es_Gloss":"sacar","_zh_Gloss":"就拔"}],"shortDef":"to say farewell","mediumDef":"to say farewell <br /><b>to take leave of, say farewell to,</b> <ref='Act.21.6'>Acts 21:6</ref>*","stepGloss":"to pay respects to","stepTransliteration":"aspazomai","count":59,"_es_Definition":"saludar (tal vez saludar con cortesía o respeto (MAT.5:47) ; dar la bienvenida ; visitar brevemente ; despedirse, decir adiós ; impv. Salúdame a (alguien)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 問候, 歡迎<br> 1a) 藉著動作與言詞<br> 1b) 藉著短時間的探訪","_zh_Definition":"1) 问候, 欢迎<br> 1a) 借着动作与言词<br> 1b) 借着短时间的探访","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"chào","_zh_tw_Gloss":"問安, 問候","_es_Gloss":"saludar/despedirse","_zh_Gloss":"问安, 问候"}]}